<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 02 at 1:53PM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...WINTER STORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT AS HEAVY SNOW CONTINUES
THROUGH EVENING COMMUTE...
WEATHER...
* Heavy snow up to 1 inch per hour continues during the afternoon.
* Additional accumulation of 2 to 3 inches from 200 PM to 500 PM.
* Snow continues after 500 PM through the evening. Temperatures
fall toward the mid 20s.
* Up to 6 inches of accumulation have been reported along the
I-69 corridor since 7 AM.
IMPACTS...
* Dangerous driving conditions due to snow covered roads and low
visibility for motorists.
&amp;&amp;
PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS...
* Motorists are urged to use caution and account for the
dangerous driving conditions by allowing extra time.
* Prepare, plan and stay informed. Visit http://go.usa.gov/c7kkP</description>
